
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/41937283/how-to-use-materializecss-in-angular-2

Answer from this repo : https://github.com/stanleyeosakul/angular-travelville
Setup Materialize CSS

    Run yarn add materialize-css@next ( or npm i materialize-css@next)

    Add Materialize CSS into .angular-cli.json ( or angular.json)

    json
        // .angular-cli.json
        {
          "apps": [
            {
              ...
              "styles": [
                "../node_modules/materialize-css/dist/css/materialize.min.css",
                "styles.css"
              ],
              "scripts": [
                "../node_modules/materialize-css/dist/js/materialize.min.js"
              ],
              ...
            }
          ]
        }

    Declare the M variable in ./src/typings.d.ts (or create the file yourself)

    typescript
    declare var M;

    Materialize CSS is now integrated into Angular!

